{"title":"BikeRadar Builds | Why Will mulleted all three of his mountain bikes","link":"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/tech/bikeradar-builds-will-soffe-mullet-bikes/","date":1685898049000,"content":"<img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620,413\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1440,959 1440w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1200,799 1200w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960,639 960w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=720,479 720w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=576,383 576w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=360,239 360w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-0e51f22.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=180,119 180w\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's mullet bikes\" title=\"Will Soffe's mullet bikes\" />                                            <p>Mullet bikes use a larger front wheel and smaller rear wheel, just like a motocross bike, to offer a business option on the trail up-front and a party at the back.</p>\n<p>Mullets have grown in popularity in recent years and I absolutely love the feel of a mullet bike.</p>\n<p>In fact, I’ve been obsessed with mulleting bikes ever since I first rode one in 2014 that I mulleted all of my personal bikes.</p>\n<p>You might be wondering, “Why on earth did he do that?”.</p>\n<p>Well, in the latest instalment of <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/tags/bikeradar-builds/\">BikeRadar Builds</a>, I’m going to walk you through each of my three <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/what-is-faster-mullet-bike-29er/\">mullet bikes</a> – a downhill bike, a trail bike and an enduro bike – to show you the different ways you could convert your bike to a mullet setup.</p>\n<p>You can also watch the video below to take a closer look – and to see where each bike shines on the trail.</p>\n<p><em>Full disclosure: you may void your warranty by converting a bike to a mullet setup, so always seek advice from the manufacturer before you start experimenting.</em></p>\n\n<h2>Will’s 2018 Commencal Supreme DH</h2>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Will’s Commencal Supreme DH in size XXL – with lots of mods!</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>The first bike I mulleted was my XXL <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/pro-bike/myriam-pompon-nicoles-commencal-supreme-dh/\">2018 Commencal Supreme DH</a>.</p>\n<p>I picked it up second-hand, and it came fitted with a pair of 27.5in wheels as standard.</p>\n<p>I’m 5ft 10in, so why the double XL bike? Well, I looked at the geometry charts, and saw that the 2018 XXL was between a 2019 medium and large, so, despite the inflated size, it’s just about right.</p>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The Fox 49er has had its 58mm offset shortened to 50mm by some Mojo Offset Reducer Crowns.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>The first thing I did was take off the RockShox Boxxer coil-sprung fork, which was fitted with a custom-tuned Avalanche open-bath cartridge. It was incredibly heavy and overdamped.</p>\n<p>I replaced it with a Fox 49er, which at the time was considered by many to be the best 29in fork you could buy.</p>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The -2 degree angle reducer headset from a Mondraker Summum keeps the head angle in the realms of sensible and allows for the fitment of a 29in front wheel and compatible fork.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>I paired it with a Hope 29er <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/mtb-axle-standards/\">Boost front wheel</a> shod in Specialized rubber.</p>\n<p>Fitting a 203mm-travel fork with a 29in front wheel raised the front wheel and slackened out the head angle to about 62 degrees, which was way too slack even for me.</p>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The high-pivot rear suspension design carries maximum speed and offers a whopping 230mm of travel.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>I slid the forks all the way through the crowns to their minimum to make the front end as low as possible. I then fitted an angle-adjust headset I had from a 2009 Mondraker Summum.</p>\n<p>Of course, it wasn’t that easy, because I then realised I had to spin the inside down in the lathe, and angle-grind the outside where it fouled on the fork-arch.</p>\n<div>\n    <i></i>\n    <div>\n  <div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-17-07865c6.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Sound deadening on the seatstays and a custom E13 chain guide help keep this bike quiet.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-19-03a549d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Saint brakes are Shimano’s DH stoppers, offering maximum power.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-22-c7b2731.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Down tube protection shields the linkage from rock strikes.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-20-91b51dc.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The Butcher Black Diamond sheds some weight compared to a full DH tyre.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-21-aeec0a5.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2018 Commencal Supreme DH\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>This fast-rolling WTB Breakout is used on hard-pack tracks.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n      </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>I also fitted a MORC, which stands for Mojo Offset Reducer Crown, made by suspension specialists Mojo Rising.</p>\n<p>This reduced the fork offset from the colossal 58mm as standard to a more manageable 50mm.</p>\n<p>After all this, I managed to snap the linkage in the <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/the-ultimate-guide-to-mountain-bike-rear-suspension-systems/\">rear suspension</a>, but thankfully Commencal sent me an updated version, which appeared after my bike was produced.</p>\n<hr /><p><strong>Why I love it:</strong> This is a bike that really shines on technical downhill tracks. The mullet setup excels on sharper, more awkward corners where the going gets flatter, and it can be hard to get a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/what-is-a-29er/\">29er</a> turned in.</p>\n<hr /><section><div>\n        \n<h2>Welcome to BikeRadar Builds</h2>\n<p>BikeRadar Builds is our occasional look at the team’s personal bikes, including custom rigs, commuters, dream builds, component testbeds and more.</p>\n<p>This is our chance to geek out about the bikes we’re riding day-to-day, and explore the thinking (or lack of it!) behind our equipment choices.</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/tech/bikeradar-builds-oscars-specialized-allez-dsw-sl-road-bike/\">Oscar’s Specialized Allez DSW SL road bike</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/bikeradar-builds-marin-alpine-trail-custom/\" target=\"_blank\">Alex’s Marin Alpine Trail custom test bike</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/bikeradar-builds-simons-planet-x-exocet-2-time-trial-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Simon’s Planet X Exocet 2 time trial bike</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/bikeradar-builds-simons-2009-giant-tcr-advanced-sl/\" target=\"_blank\">Simon’s 2009 TCR Advanced SL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/bikeradar-builds-jacks-refurbished-touring-tandem-cecil/\" target=\"_blank\">Jack’s refurbished touring tandem, Cecil</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/jack-luke-road-bike-lee-cooper/\">Jack’s fabulously flexible 1994 Lee Cooper 653</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/bikeradar-builds-mason-bokeh-gravel-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">George’s Mason Bokeh gravel bike</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/genesis-croix-de-fer-853-br-builds/\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew’s Genesis Croix de Fer 853</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/santa-cruz-chameleon-singlespeed/\" target=\"_blank\">Tom’s Santa Cruz Chameleon mullet singlespeed</a></li>\n</ul><p>\n\n    </p></div>\n    </section><h2>Will’s 2019 Cannondale Habit</h2>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The Cannondale Habit AL looks surprisingly at home with a mullet setup.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>Away from the world of downhill, I often like to go for a more chilled trail ride, and when I do, I pick my Cannondale Habit.</p>\n<p>It’s a large-size 2019 Habit 4 AL I <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/how-to-buy-a-used-or-second-hand-bike-online/\">bought second-hand</a> as a frame. It came with a Cane Creek Double Barrel coil, which I hated: not enough rebound control and it topped-out horribly.</p>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The 160mm Fox 36 fork is stiff enough for serious trail riding.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>I rode the Habit for a while and found it fast and efficient, but I knew I wanted a bike that was more playful so, you guessed it, I decided to mullet it.</p>\n<p>I fitted a 27.5in rear wheel and a longer eye-to-eye shock. The standard shock is 210mm, but the Fox Float X2 Factory is 216mm.</p>\n<p></p><div>\n    <i></i>\n    <div>\n  <div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-32-dcd41cf.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The Spank Spike bars are 780mm wide.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-28-6d191d2.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>A get-out-of-jail kit includes patches, inflator and tyre levers.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-25-8792e66.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>A Fox Float X2 with custom travel reducers still adds 8mm of travel to the Habit.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-30-a0894f1.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>203mm Galfer DiscShark rotors front and rear are quiet and almost flex-free.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-29-3ad9726.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The Shimano Saint front caliper and Zee lever provide ample stopping power.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-26-bc0cf60.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>A Shimano XT drivetrain with cheaper SLX chainring keeps things wallet-friendly.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n      </div>\n</div>\n</div>\nI put travel limiters on the shock shaft to prevent the bike bottoming out on itself, but it still develops 8mm more travel than standard, bumping it up from 130mm to 138mm.\n<p>This also means the bottom bracket height in the ‘high’ setting is pretty close to the standard BB height in the ‘low’ setting.</p>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2019 Cannondale Habit\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Drink tea, shred gnar. How British.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Max Wilman / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<hr /><p><strong>Why I love it:</strong> On jump-filled tracks, the bike is easier to drift, because of the smaller rear wheel and the lower BB height. It’s easier to pop into a manual and feels more playful with the smaller rear wheel.</p>\n<hr /><h2>Will’s 2014 Specialized Enduro SX</h2>\n<div>\n    <img width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The mini-mullet setup on Will’s 2014 Specialized Enduro SX pairs a 27.5in front wheel with a 26in rear, offering the rider a mix of responsiveness and stable handling.</span></figcaption><span> <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i></span></div>\n<p>This is perhaps the strangest and rarest bike in my collection. It’s a 100mm-travel, limited-edition Specialized Enduro SX from 2014 in size ‘long’.</p>\n<p>Specialized only made around 100 of these (or so I’m told) and I always wanted one, ever since I saw Specialized pro rider Mitch Ropelato compete in the Sea Otter dual-slalom on one. When I saw this frame for sale close to where I live, I had to buy it.</p>\n<p></p><div>\n    <i></i>\n    <div>\n  <div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-3-cd780ea.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The 120mm-travel Fox 36 fork deals with front-end traction.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-11-35d45cc.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The compression settings on this bike are firm for maximum efficiency.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-4-073f236.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's mullet bikes_-4\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>100mm travel on the shock via an aggressive 2:1 shock actuation ratio keeps the rear end taut and responsive.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-5-c731d23.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>This bike has long and light 175mm XTR cranks with a large 36t chainring for fast gated starts.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n      </div>\n</div>\n</div>\nThe bike is set up for 4x and dual slalom, and I’ve competed on it twice in the Malvern Classic, where I won in 2020 and came second behind Scott Beaumont in 2021.\n<p>The bike came with 26in wheels, but I fitted a 27.5in wheel into the 26in-specific Fox 36 Factory fork to make a mini-mullet setup. The fork itself has been dropped to 120mm travel with an aftermarket air shaft.</p>\n<div>\n    <i></i>\n    <div>\n  <div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-2-654f629.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>Handguards are a must for dual slalom, where the poles swipe savagely at riders’ fingers and can even grab a brake lever. These AVS examples are the same as used by three-time Enduro World Series winner Sam Hill.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-13-20e8170.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The handguards have seen some action…</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-12-2554d7c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>ODI grips are a sticky classic. Good grips are a must when yanking hard on the handlebars off the start.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-10-d1d9c36.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>This bike is dripping in carbon and titanium parts such as this headset spacer and stem pinch-bolt.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-1-c0e9228.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Top tube on Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's mullet bikes_-1\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>From 2014, the Enduro SX is an enduring classic still used today by 4x racers such as Scott Beaumont.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-8-4dab7fd.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The SRAM 7-speed DH block and short-cage derailleur give confident shifts under full-power sprinting.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n          <div>\n        \n<figure><div>\n    <img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2023/06/Will-Soffes-mullet-bikes-9-8a913f3.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C723\" width=\"556\" height=\"723\" alt=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" title=\"Will Soffe's 2014 Specialized Enduro SX\" /></div>    <figcaption><div>\n    <figcaption><span>The chainguide has been ditched to save valuable grams.</span>\n    </figcaption><span>\n                    <i>Felix Smith / Our Media</i>\n            </span>\n</div>\n\n    </figcaption></figure></div>\n      </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>The advantage of the mini-mullet – 27.5in at the front, 26in at the back – is it makes the steering a little calmer and slackens the head angle.</p>\n<p>It handles bumps slightly more confidently and is easier to drift thanks to the extra grip from the larger front wheel.</p>\n<hr /><p><strong>Why I love it:</strong> This bike is perfect for sculpted jumps, as well as manual duties. It’s really easy to move around underneath me and I can pop into a manual with the short back end and 26in rear wheel. The 27.5in front wheel adds stability due to its greater rotating mass, and adds some extra cornering traction on the front end.</p>\n<hr /><p> </p>","author":"Will Soffe","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"cdfa4796cc4c1b14a351becc4902bc49c2c08473255560d914e1d112750ca58a","category":"Cycling"}